column1: What will happen next regarding New York Governor Andrew Cuomo?
column4: Cuomo will either resign as governor or announce that he will resign as governor
column5: ['Cuomo will announce that he will not seek reelection as governor in 2022', 'Cuomo will either resign as governor or announce that he will resign as governor', 'Cuomo will be removed from office by an impeachment trial', 'None of these will occur before 1 April 2022']

Resignation just announced. Competition closed.
Cuomo has announced that he's stepping aside
As the surroundings implode, so will Cuomo. Time's up!
Prison should be on the list.

- Top aide resigns (https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/us/melissa-derosa-top-aide-to-gov-cuomo-resigns/ar-AAN5ArS?OCID=ansmsnnews11) - He's trying to cut a deal to stay on for the remainder of his term (https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/us/cuomo-trying-to-cut-a-deal-to-avoid-impeachment-source-says/ar-AAN6Uve) - Lt Gov making her takeover plans (https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/new-york-lt-gov-kathy-hochul-is-preparing-to-take-over-for-andrew-cuomo-report/ar-AAN6s92)

My priors here are that Cuomo is extraordinarily stubborn and scornful of public opinion, executive office holders of both parties have learned they can just wait out scandals in an era of non-stop news and fickle public concern.

Melissa DeRosa, Cuomo's top aide and confidante, resigned tonight. She was involved in helping cover the full extent of the nursing homes deaths at the height of the pandemic and also led efforts to retaliated against the first woman who accused the governor of sexual harassment. I think this increases the odds of the governor resigning instead of waiting to be impeached but Mr Cuomo's hubris is big enough to fight the inevitable to the end before quitting.

Cuomo is going to try to cut a deal. Promising not to run in 2022 won't be enough, but he may try it before resigning. He gains nothing by forcing the legislature to impeach him which it will do if he does not resign.
Well, I wish I didn't enter this one. I'm really unsure what to do here.
first polling shows 70% of new yorkers think he should resign, but i believe he will wait it out and see if people lose interest and move on....

It's an awfully long time until next election and even in the context of this question's closing. That's why I see his removal more urgent than expected. This in conjunction with the new criminal filing against him.
HIs own party wants him gone - something will happen. Removing any chance of 4th bin.
Sorry, I thought I had an independently different forecast from my last one based on new information but it turns out my probabilities haven't changed.

Nobody can make Cuomo resign, and his history and personality do not arouse hope that he will do so. There are probably enough votes in the Assembly to impeach him, but they'll need some pretend deliberations as they prepare to file, docket, and vote on the articles. The Honourable Members will have to fit this carnival in with other legislative business and also take the usual long and frequent breaks from their exertions.

Very interesting question. I don't think nothing will happen. So 4th choice if attempt to remove from office fails. So that's one thing I will look into - is there any data to use to predict how likely impeachment trial success if attempted.
This is a very interesting question. But I have no idea and so to indicate that all outcomes equal.

I'm starting to see that the Dems need Cuomo gone - they can’t afford to give the Republican contestant for Governor next year any extra ammo. My guess is he will be pressured into stepping down and save himself from impeachment but he's still very defensive and holding his position for now.

The impeachment process is speeding up and it sounds like there may be enough opposition for him to be impeached now. I'm leaning to favor the middle two buckets with the thought process that Cuomo may resign if he looks likely to be impeached.

"None of these will occur" -- Part of prediction making is looking at history. Delaying has worked well for Cuomo in the past, including this year when he refused to resign in March and his poll numbers gradually went back up due to his Covid response and the passage of time.

Everything feels to be on the table and the impeachment process could be swift. Granted, status quo will likely prevail, this is a moment of delicious uncertainty. https://open.spotify.com/episode/64ZulgPoftYl3J6rSukm1A?si=4ZPCMokLRNiy8KQAJ3Pj1w&dl_branch=1
Biden is saying he should resign. Reducing confidence in the last bucket on the latest news.

I love when news shakes up a stale question. A light overview: https://apnews.com/article/cuomo-sexual-harassment-what-to-know-2628bf06d048720cc265fa66771a5976?utm_source=Sailthru&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=Aug4_MorningWire&utm_term=Morning%20Wire%20Subscribers

Cuomo is as defiant and unrepentant as ever. I'm increasing the probability of impeachment because of remarks made by Speaker Carl Heastie: “the Governor has lost the confidence of the Assembly Democratic majority and that he can no longer remain in office.” However, it's far from clear that the Assembly has any timeline for finishing their own investigation or starting impeachment proceedings, and whether the votes are there to remove Cuomo from office.

NYT reporting that Assembly Speaker, Carl Heastie, says "they will move expeditiously and look to conclude impeachment investigation as quickly as possible" Haeastie wouldn't move quick enough on impeachment regarding nursing home deaths and other decisions Cuomo made at the height of the pandemic but they will move quickly on sexual harassment report.
Dems turn on their own. Interesting that Pelosi made a statement - what's it to her? Is there someone in the wings they want to put in that role?
New York news is covering the sexual harassment cases in great detail. Probe concludes Cuomo harassed 11 women. Biden says he should resign.
The rowboat is gonna be rocking back and forth for me a little bit while I digest today's news.
https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-cuomo-resign-sexual-harassment-report

Pres. Biden just said Cuomo should resign after NY AG made her report on sexual harassment investigation public. Cuomo is going to fight, foolishly, but it's going to take some time for him to realize he's toxic and he cannot mend the damage done. He was able to stay afloat all this time, in part because the party itself let him run with it as they worked on negotiating the budget then buying some time for the report to be completed. But they all had to know. It's another shrewd political game. Things are so bad in NY that de Blasio now thinks he can run for governor.

Report of the Attorney-General says the Guv has been and remains a serial jerk. No one is surprised by this. Nonetheless, there will be much pearl-clutching in the New York State Assembly, followed almost immediately by outraged outrage from the Rs while the Ds pretend to be dead. If this sounds familiar, the rehearsal for it was two remarkably similar episodes down in DC over the past several years, from the other side of the aisle. Political cowardice is not a partisan monopoly.

follow the money

I regret not pinpointing which of my previous forecasts included base rates. It was hard work and I'm probably not going to render the same percentages if I tried again. This update adjusts back to my gut feelings, putting myself into the governor's shoes if I were to resign. However, I have a hunch that it is more likely to resign than announce you are not running for re-election; I think resignations are far more common than admitting that you are powerless and not running.
NY Assembly begins issuing subpoenas for an impeachment trial.
He's likely to announce that he will not seek reelection, then actually go for election.
Cuomo's smart move would be to announce that he is not seeking re-election. It looks like he could have a difficult time in a primary against the NY Attorney General.

2% each month with current level of criticisim. May 25 - Forty-nine percent of voters surveyed last week by the Siena College Research Institute said Mr. Cuomo shouldn’t resign, a slight decrease from the 51% of respondents who in April said the governor should stay. https://www.wsj.com/articles/half-of-new-yorker-voters-stand-by-gov-andrew-cuomo-poll-finds-11621848600

Cuomo's number one goal is to outlast as governor compared to his father. Save for something truly malicious emerging (and the needed media attention), I cannot imagine it would lead to an issue. Furthermore, in New York City, he is still well-liked compared to other NYC Politicians who would have an easier time getting reelected.
Since Covid ended we haven’t heard too much about the case…

He seems to be edging toward expressing a desire to spend more time with the family. When government or corporate executives say this, nobody ever asks the family what they want. It is possible to wonder about this.
He'll be bored and want to control his destiny.
CNTP - 8/1/0,5 each month
He is in big trouble and getting worse but will not stick around to be impeached.

I think if polling results indicate Cuomo will lose an election badly, I will announce that he won't seek re-election. I think that the Southern District DA will not announce impeachment before April 2022 (unless the prosecutor decides to run for office herself, which would further delay the case).

Talking to a number of New Yorkers over the past week, the solid consensus is that the state General Assembly is in disarray and does not have the ability, at least at the moment, to mount an impeachment. Additionally, they are fairly confident that unless the emerging scandals really heat up and are compounded by additional scandals it is highly unlikely Cuomo will resign. Unanimous agreement was that he will not seek re-election. Of course, these are just opinion, but all of these people are involved in some level of New York politics, Democratic and Republican. Making slight modifications in my forecast as a result.

While issues are piling up for Governor Cuomo (i.e. more sexual harassment allegations, COVID nursing home scandal, increased unpopularity, etc.), considering his statements and personality, at the moment, it remains unlikely he will resign. Impeachment does not appear to be gaining enough traction at the moment. The most likely outcome by April 1st is Cuomo announces he is not seeking re-election in 2022. I am reducing my "None" forecast slightly to reallocate to "resign" and "removed" based on the increase pressures Cuomo is facing and to account for unforeseen issues that may arise later in the year.

Even for amurricans, New Yorkers have a short attention span. Until something else breaks, nobody will think about Merry Andrew very much. In addition, he is blessed with boundless arrogance and a firm faith in the tendency of his constituents to vote Democrat no matter what. It will be difficult for even a reasonably attractive R, if there still were any, to win statewide office here. One or two Ds will mount a loud but fruitless intra-party squall. It will die down and he will be re-elected. Think of New Yorkers as Texans with better pizza.

It is not obvious that there is a real legal case to impeach him (and maybe that doesn’t matter, but it might). His power is not based on being liked so much as being elected. However, he probably can’t win nomination again.
Option 5: Cuomo dies of COVID
Cuomo's time is limited as the charges mount and Investigations progress.
he is a Democrat with a Democratic legislation, they are not going to do anything against him.

He seems to be sailing through, a plausible explanation is that legislators made a deal with him (just take a look at the state budget they were able to pull off) in exchange for the budget they wanted. It's a budget one highly doubts Cuomo would have signed in any other political atmosphere.

I don't understand the crowd confidence in bucket 1 or lack of confidence in buckets 2 and 3. But I'm not informed on NY politics so hedging toward the crowd a bit, though I think option 4 is the most likely outcome so increased that to a bit over 50%. From what I've seen a majority of state legislators have called for him to resign, so I feel like options 2 and 3 are decently plausible.
Impeachment unlikely. Only 8 US governors have ever been impreached

Cuomo has a lot of political capital from leading the NY coronavirus response; his scandals will slowly draw down that capital, but are not severe enough to remove him from office before the end of his term.
News surrounding this issue is becoming less and less in the news networks

The Honourable Gentleman says he's being persecuted because he's not in with the political In Crowd. This may not work: His daddy was the Governor; he was a member of Clinton's cabinet; and he is married to a Kennedy. On the other hand, he saw the Big Lie work for the President-Eject and may think it will serve him as well. One might point out politely that it didn't work for M. Petits-Doigts in New York.
If there will be more pressure from the party he might resign (unlikely) , but hard to see him seek re-election
He's a swine, and will use the public's money for his own defense, for as long as he can.

Cuomo seems unlikely to be reelected given that a majority of New Yorkers want him to resign. Still, if he were going to resign, he probably would have already. The most likely scenario would seem one in which Cuomo allows someone else to seek the governorship in 2022 by not seeking reelection during the democratic primary process.

Cuomo has no intention of resigning, but if additional information comes out he might be forced to admit he will not seek re-election. But his ego will not have him voluntarily step down. Saying he won't seek re-election is the closest thing we will get to an admission of wrongdoing.
Hedging toward the crowd.

New York Attorney General Leticia James' is busy! She is / will be coordinating with NYS and federal investigators regarding Trump, in addition to Cuomo's mishandling of covid-19 in nursing homes and allegations of harassment of female members of his staff. It will be late 2020 (at least) before any announcements are made on the Cuomo investigations. Cuomo will have time to ride out this quiet period while the investigations are underway and later will announce that he will decline to run again in lieu of a reelection campaign. Cuomo knows that a reelection campaign will damn his legacy if AG James' investigations don't damn him first.

Resignation seems likely. While he has enough popularity with NY Democrats to avoid impeachment, there is a slightly greater chance he could face pressure from the establishment to resign for the party's sake. Cuomo lacks complete support and has a toxic glow to his name, which will certainly cost him support from all of the younger demographic and make him all but unelectable. Without party support, it will be financially beneficial for him to resign and keep his war chest versus spending it all on a fruitless election attempt.
In US history: P(RESIGN) = (37 + 15) / 1250 = 0.0416 P(Impeached) = 8 / 1250 = 0.0064

I haven't been following this very closely but my perception is that he has no intention of giving in and I think unfortunately partisanship has ultimately been shown to be stronger when it comes to misbehavior recently.
Vegas odds makers say he will stay in office... https://www.casino.org/news/andrew-cuomo-odds-suggest-new-york-governor-will-remain/ But do not say-- yet-- that he will NOT seek reelection.
I don't think Cuomo will be impeached or that he will resign. It's a black box guess whether he will announce he's not running before April 1, 2022.
